            <bug_when>2008-09-18 09:39:10 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>For IE browsers a special placeholder &quot;blank.gif&quot; located at the &quot;qx/static&quot; folder is used to equip specific elements (e.g. the widely used &quot;protector&quot; element) with a background-image.
The URL to this placeholder image is wrong, leading at least IE6 to freeze when loading an application which uses this image multiple times.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>5573</commentid>
            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2008-09-18 09:40:22 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Fixed this issue with Revision #16396.

The image &quot;qx/static/blank.gif&quot; hasn&#39;t got a &quot;#asset&quot; directive and was (partly) wrong referenced. This led the IE6 to freeze completely. I guess the browser waits for a timeout and because this image is requested many times for IE browsers (e.g. every &quot;protector&quot; element has it) this blows up the browser.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
